<dl id="s14023e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us14" href="#s14023e">Oxen of the Sun: </a><a href="../../FF/unbs/s14all.htm#s14023e">sector 23(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> he nighed it so nigh</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">And in the city of Sarras he converted a king whose name was Evelake. And so this king came with Joseph into this land: and always he was busy to be there as the Sancgreal was, and on a time <mark>he nighed it so nigh</mark> that our Lord was displeased with him, but ever he followed it more and more, till God struck him almost blind. <small> Thomas Malory, <a name="TMMD" href="/udra/udex.htm#TMMD"><cite title="source">Morte Darthur</cite></a> (1868), 367</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
